The paper discusses a method for incorporating human intuition and domain knowledge in model-free machine learning, specifically in the context of deep reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on continuous control problems, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions experiments involving image-based tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
